Durban - Police have arrested a 29-year-old man, wanted in connection with a spate of murders and attempted murders at the Glebelands Hostel in uMlazi. The man is set to make an appearance in the uMlazi Magistrate’s Court after he was found in possession of a .38 special revolver and a dagger at the Glebelands hostel at the weekend. Police were patrolling the area when they were informed about a group of people who had firearms. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, police spokesperson said officers went in search of the group but did not find anything on them. “Later on, the officers became suspicious about the person who gave them information and he was approached and searched. He was found in possession of a revolver with its serial number erased. There were five live rounds from the firearm and a dagger was also recovered from him. The suspect was charged with possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition,” Zwane said. Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner,  welcomed the arrest of the suspect. “Our police officers are still conducting their patrols at Glebelands hostel to get rid of criminal activities in the area. Residents of hostel must work together with the police in bringing peace and stability in their hostel. They must not allow criminals to hide with unlicensed firearms as they might become dangerous to their lives, he said. Meanwhile, the bail applications of seven men, arrested in relation to ongoing violence at the hostel, are expected to resume in the Durban Magistrate's Court on Monday. Sergeant Bhekukwazi Mdweshu and co-accused Vukani Mcobothi, Khayelihle Mbuthuma, Wonderboy Hlophe, Matlala Mdweshu Ntshangase, Mahliphiza Mkhize and Mondli Mthethwa, were arrested by police during intense investigations. Daily News